Yea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil: for thou art with me; thy rod and thy staff, they comfort me.
Walking through the valley of the shadow of death, a single steel water bottle in my hand.
"Thou preparest a table before me in the presence of mine enemies: thou anointest my head with oil; my steel water bottle runneth over."

It is often said that Christians weeping for their dead relatives and friends is only due to a lack of faith, because their souls are now reunited with God, but this is not true. Death is a catastrophe, not a liberation. It is unnatural. A dead man is not fully a man.

Spirit and body belong to each other, their separation is a perversion of man's nature. Death was not created by God, it was a result of the Fall. It is unnatural for a man to be mortal. Seeing death as good in any way is foreign to Scripture.

- Protopresbyter Georges Florovsky

I weep and sob when I think of death and see our beauty, created in God's image, lying in a grave, mutilated, disfigured, shapeless. What is this mystery, what happened to us? How did we surrender to rotting? How did we connect ourselves to death?

- St. John Damascene

I think the big issue here is this: is life able to exist outside of death? Is everything good in/of life connected somehow with death? If the answer is no, then death is just useless and brings nothing good, life's beauty does not have to rely on death's beauty imo
Death is external to man, not a part of his organism. Death is a machine that man has connected himself to, and he can also be disconnected from it.

The phrase "He Who Sings Means No Harm" is very correct. No matter what terrain you do it in, you pretty much give up any strategic advantage you had over possible opponents, reveal your exact position, give them time to draw weaponry etc.

Like any moment of surprise is eliminated, this even works with animals, I always sing when walking through tall grass so any snakes move away before I step through their lounging spots. Bears, boars, wolves, etc. also evade you, song makes your journey safer.
